notesStmt.note: Title from caption title (f. 1r), where work is ascribed to Padre Frà Paolo Servita.
Same text as UPenn Ms. Codex 559.

msContents.summary: Work on the government of Venice, questionably attributed to the Venetian Servite monk Paolo Sarpi and supposedly written by him for the Inquistori di Stato, the highest decision-making body in the Venetian Republic. First published in 1681 under title: Opinione del padre Paolo servita, come debba governarsi la Republica veneziana per haverse il perpetuo dominio.

msItem.title: Opinione ... In qual modo debba governarsi la republica Venezia internamente et esternamente per havere perpetuo dominio
msItem.author: Sarpi, Paolo, 1552-1623,

supportDesc.extent: 84 leaves : 196 x 140 (175 x 102) mm. bound to 200 x 145 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 84; 1-84; contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto (some numerals trimmed off).

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

binding.p: Contemporary vellum (Zacour-Hirsch) with village scene painted on lower cover; faint ink sketches of human figures on upper cover.
